PAL20L8
32016 PC/Z80 BOARD
(C) 1986 GEORGE SCOLARO
ADDRESS DECODER PAL FOR 32016 MEMORY SPACE
LA23 LA22 LA21 LA08 LA09 /RSTO /ISEL IA1 IA2 /IOR /IOW GND
IRESET /RD /ICU /RAMS /EPROM /SREQC /INT86 /RSTI /INT32 /PPORT SWAP VCC

; NOTE /IOR NOT USED IN PAL
; NOTE /RSTO NOT USED IN PAL

IF (VCC) ICU	= LA23 * LA22 * LA21 * LA09 * /LA08

IF (VCC) RAMS	= /SWAP * /LA23 * /LA22 * /LA21
		+  SWAP *  LA23 * /LA22 * /LA21

IF (VCC) EPROM	= SWAP * /LA23 * /LA22 * /LA21

IF (VCC) PPORT	= LA23 * LA22 * LA21 * /LA09 * /LA08

IF (VCC) SREQC	= ISEL * IA1 * IA2 * IOW
		+ RSTI
		+ IRESET

IF (VCC) INT86 = LA23 * LA22 * LA21 * /LA09 * LA08 * RD

IF (VCC) RSTI	= ISEL * IA1 * /IA2 * IOW	;IBM SOFTWARE RESET
		+ RSTI * /INT32 * /IRESET	;LATCH RESET IF NOT PON RESET

IF (VCC) INT32 = ISEL * /IA1 * IA2 * IOW

FUNCTION TABLE
/RD SWAP LA23 LA22 LA21 LA09 LA08 /ISEL IA1 IA2 /IOW IRESET
/ICU /RAMS /EPROM /PPORT /INT86 /SREQC /RSTI /INT32
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
X X HHHHL X XX X X L H H H H X X X	;TEST ICU SELECT
X L LLLXX X XX X X H L H H H X X X	;TEST RAMS IF SWAP LOW
X H HLLXX X XX X X H L H H H X X X	;TEST RAMS IF SWAP HIGH
X H LLLXX X XX X X H H L H H X X X	;TEST EPROM IF SWAP HIGH
X X HHHLL X XX X X H H H L H X X X	;TEST PPORT SELECT
L X HHHLH X XX X X H H H H L X X X	;TEST INT86 SIGNAL
X X XXXXX L HH L X X X X X X L X H	;TEST SREQC AND NO INT32
X X XXXXX L HL L X X X X X X L L H	;TEST RSTI -> SREQC BUT NO INT32
X X XXXXX L LH L L X X X X X H H L	;TEST INT32 SIGNAL
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
This pal generates the chip selects for RAM, EPROM, ICU and PPORT on the
PD32. The signal INT86 is a software signal from the PD32 that both generates
an interrupt on the host (if connected) and sets a status request flip flop
that the host may poll. The pal also generates the software reset, software
interrupt and SREQC signals. The host may at anytime reset the PD32 via a
write to a special port. The SREQC signal is used by the host to clear the
status request flip flop (indicating that it is servicing the PD32 interrupt).
